  Prerequirities
-------------------------

This application is just test app.

For debian

You can install mojolicious and libvalidation-class-perl debian packages 
from http://www.volf.eu/debian/pool/main/libmojolicious-perl_3.11-1_all.deb)
and http://www.volf.eu/debian/pool/main/libvalidation-class-perl_5.83-1_all.deb

and other packages are from debian stable

aptitude install libdbi-perl libdbd-pg-perl libdbd-mysql-perl libintl-perl libdatetime-locale-perl libdatetime-perl libdatetime-timezone-perl mysql-server-5.1

Non debian

To install mysql see your distribution documentation.

To install mojolicious from CPAN see http://mojolicio.us/ documentation

You can install modules from CPAN

  DateTime;
  DBD::Pg
  DBD::mysql
  DBI;
  Encode;
  File::Basename
  File::Spec::Functions
  Locale::Messages
  POSIX
  Scalar::Util
  Test::More


  Download sources
-------------------------

git clone git://github.com/norbertvolf/treemanager.git

or download zip from 

https://github.com/norbertvolf/treemanager/zipball/master


  Create database
-------------------------

Create database and put script/sql/rev0001.sql to database
Then setup database in tree_manager.conf 

  Run application
-------------------------

You can use mojolicious startes example morbo scripts/tree_manager and http://localhost:3000/tree in your browser

